  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To assess the role of germline polymorphisms in xenobiotic metabolism genes in toxicity
      profile.

      To assess the role of germline polymorphisms in genes associated with DNA repair, p53 tumor
      suppressor gene and angiogenesis pathway in predicting recurrence and survival in gastric
      cancer patients treated with adjuvant chemotherapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
